# 8. 相棒になるために

An: (I have to apologize to Kohane... Properly too...)
Akito: Hey...
An: Hm, Akito? You're early today.
Akito: School finished early so...
An: Okay.
An: I should say thank you, for yesterday...
Akito: Thank you... For what?
An: You opened my eyes to the fact I was holding Kohane back by being so overprotective.
An: So, I want to say thank you for that.
Akito: Meh, it wasn't a big deal.
An: Stop acting so cool and just accept my thanks.
An: Honestly, I'm nervous about telling her how I thought she needed my guidance and protection...
Akito: ...
An: But this is something I have to do if we're gonna stick together. Even if she gets angry with me...
An: If I don't have the courage to do this, it'll mean I don't deserve to share the stage with her.
Akito: Shiraishi...
An: I think we have the potential to outshine RAD WEEKEND, but I have to apologize to Kohane and patch things up with her before we can do that...
Akito: Uh, huh...
Toya: You two are pretty early...
Kohane: Or are we the late ones...?
Akito: No, we got here ahead of time.
An: Kohane!
Kohane: Huh?
An: I'm so sorry about yesterday!!
An: And the things I said about covering for you... I've been so overprotective this whole time!
An: Akito made me realize that I wasn't treating you fairly, like an equal...
Kohane: ...
An: I used to perform solo with the goal of surpassing RAD WEEKEND in mind.
An: For the longest time, I couldn't find anyone who I thought had it in them to join me on this path... Until you came along.
An: You're an awesome singer, Kohane. I want to keep performing with you and realize that dream.
An: I believe all of this, even now. Especially now!
An: When you weren't sure about something, you leaned on me and asked me for advice...
An: That made me really happy. And I didn't want that to end...
An: But it ended with yesterday happening...
An: I failed you as your partner.
An: I should've believed in you more and helped you grow...
Kohane: An...
An: But... I want us to be together, Kohane!
An: I want us to perform together! I want to be your partner!
An: I want you to believe in us too! Because I really believe in you, Kohane!
An: So please, will you sing with me on that stage again?
Kohane: An, of course...
Kohane: You don't have to blame yourself for yesterday. It's a fact that I just wasn't able to sing until the very end.
Kohane: It wasn't right for me to be so reliant on you too, but I didn't know what to do now.
Kohane: I talked to different friends about it and they all assured me that I'll improve as long as I work at it. That I'll eventually be able to pull my own weight.
Kohane: But I want to go beyond that. I want to be a fully-fledged member of this group, who proudly sings with you, An.
Kohane: And I want the four of us to realize our dream together.
An: Kohane...
Kohane: If I got the crowd as fired up as the rest of you did at the event yesterday...
Kohane: I'm sure we would've had the best performance there!
Kohane: It might take me some time before I stop falling behind or slipping up...
Kohane: But I want nothing more than to keep singing with you, An!
An: Yeah... Yeah! Thanks, Kohane!
Kohane: W-Wait, An?! I wasn't prepared for a hug...!
An: I'm so happy, I couldn't help it...!
Akito: See. Told you they'd sort it out.
Toya: Indeed, you were right...
Akito: Wait, did you say something to her?
Toya: I gave her some advice as a teammate. That's all...
An: So which event should we go for next? I brought a few flyers.
MEIKO: Oh, there are so many to choose from...
An: And they all look awesome! I don't know which one to pick.
Kohane: Then how about... This one? An outdoor gig at Miyamasuzaka next month?
Akito: An outdoor gig... This one draws a big crowd and features really good groups too.
Toya: And performing outside could be nice for a change.
An: Sounds like everyone's in! I'll sign us up.
An: Now that we know what we're doing, let's start preparing for it!
Kohane: Yeah!
MEIKO: Oh, everyone. Would you mind if Rin and Len joined your practice sessions?
MEIKO: They've been telling me how much they'd really like to sing with you.
An: Sure, no problem!
MEIKO: Thank you. They should be here soon with Miku.
An: Oh, right... Hey, Kohane...
An: If I miss a cue at the next event...
An: Could you cover for me?
Kohane: An... Sure, I can do that!
An: Thanks, partner! I'm countin' on ya!
MEIKO: (Hehe. They're becoming a good team.)
MEIKO: (Something tells me that they'll make their dreams come true too.)
